 the Heartshard’s legend says a lie will cut the mouth that speaks it, so I ask you to hold your fulgurite and speak clean with me when we listen together. I want no name from you that you did not earn in truth, and I will note any instrument’s color drift in the Prismarium’s record, even if it offends my superiors, because glass that sings on a clear sky is a wound, and wounds fester when they are hidden.\"}\n      ],\n      \"choices\": [\n        {\"id\": \"C1\", \"title\": \"Ride the chain’s breath and swing the riggers to safety\", \"text\": \"You choose the rhythm of the harbor over brute force, and you signal the crew to breathe with the chain’s click instead of fighting it. You wedge a sprung board against the ratchet casing, take the strain on your chain-hook gauntlet, and count heartbeats until the tide’s lift eases the jam’s teeth a whisper. You call for one rigger to kick wide on the next hush and take the swing, and you promise you’ll carry the bruises yourself in the House of Weights if the arc goes hard. The second breath you use to reset the counterweight with a pry and a curse, and the third is for the youngest, whose boots drum terror into the steel until your voice turns the drum into a song counted in fours. You speak to fear like an old neighbor, and you bring the first body to the catwalk, then the second, then the third, each one cussing your orders but hugging the grating with a gratitude that tastes of salt and not tears.\", \"outcome\": \"The lift stabilizes with a groan like a tired ox, and the ratchet teeth spit out their lie to admit the truth of your patience. The three riggers collapse on the catwalk swearing loudly that they never doubted you, which is a lie you forgive because the city is listening for worse. Wardens on the far platform nod despite themselves, and dockers murmur your name like a small oath that holds for a night, and the jam becomes a story about breath and timing instead of a dirge. You find a scored pawl with fresh resin grit in its bite, a strange sign that someone’s dirty thumb was near, and you pocket a sliver not to steal but to show a lens. The House of Weights slate rings off its last tremor as you step back onto solid planks, and for a moment the harbor feels like a chest that has remembered how to breathe.\"},\n        {\"id\": \"C2\", \"title\": \"Argue to keep the Nine Mouths open under lantern discipline\", \"text\": \"At Windward Bastion you ask Sorev Katch to hear a docker’s calculus, and you speak like someone who has counted how quickly fear empties cupboards. You say that if the chains all lift at once without cause the city will read it as panic, and panic calls pirates like blood calls sharks, so better to hold the mouths at a stagger and make a map of steadiness in light. You propose coded lantern intervals that read calm to pilots and stern warning to smugglers, a pattern the League of Lanterns has used to keep storms from becoming stampedes. You promise to put dock crews on double checks and to have the House of Weights open its doors for night calibration, so nobody can say a shaved scale was the reason a man died today. You give him the shape of the Beacon’s bitten note, not as proof enough to shut a city, but as a reason to keep hands off the panic levers while you climb to listen for more.\", \"outcome\": \"Sorev’s jaw works like a man chewing a nail, but he gives you the nod he saves for plans he will accept and later pretend were his, and your lantern pattern cuts through dusk like a firm hand on a frightened shoulder. The Wardens hold the chains in staggered lift and lower with crews at their posts instead of at the taverns, and smugglers who love a muddle find no muddle to love. The League’s silhouettes on the towers trade measured signals that make even the gulls settle, and at the House of Weights a queue forms for honest calibrations under oil that does not flicker. You do not win his promise never to close the harbor, but you win his promise not to do it on a rumor, and that distinction keeps fish on tables and hands on safe tasks through the night. When you leave the Bastion, you carry no writ, only a sense that your word sat in the right ear at the right time and tilted nothing but fear.\"},\n        {\"id\": \"C3\", \"title\": \"Swear an honest ear with Liora Fen in the Beacon’s galleries\", \"text\": \"Under the Beacon’s singing skin, where galleries curve like a shell’s inner lip, you stand with Liora Fen and take out the fulgurite shard you wear by your heart. You tell her you will not swear to secrets that make the Dockers blind, and you will not take an oath that lets the Conclave paint over a crack with light, and she answers that a true oath is a lantern, not a curtain. You both touch the shard and feel it warm, not with heat, but with intention, and you speak aloud that what you hear together you will carry together to the Court of Echoing Shells if it proves to be a lie large enough to wake glass. You say the names of those who might be harmed if you tangle this wrong—the riggers you hauled, the pilots who trust the Reef, the marsh-wives who read knots—and you tie each name to the promise that you will not be used. The Beacon hums as if it is eavesdropping on your small brave sound, and you and Liora lean your heads as close to the glass as two conspirators and two servants of the city can.\", \"outcome\": \"The residue is there like a bruise, and together you find its edge, a harmonic that should spiral clean but breaks as if a hand clapped over a mouth at the moment of vow. Liora’s lenses bloom a color-shift not natural to clear weather, a distorting mauve that the Prismarium’s charts name misharmonized oath-lens, and you feel the fulgurite pulse as if it agrees with the diagnosis. You do not have a culprit, but you have a place and a time in the music, and Liora drafts the record in clean script with her own name under it, which is a brave thing for a Conclave tender to do. The Faith’s doctrine whispers through your memory that oaths and storms share a spine, and you think of the Court’s shells keening for liars, and you know where this will have to be heard if the city is to heal without opening a new wound. You descend from the galleries with your jaw set and your shard warm, carrying nothing in your hands but a note in a song and the obligation to follow it to the next verse.\"}\n      ],\n      \"connections\": {\"previous\": [], \"next\": [\"M2\"]},\n      \"rewards\": [\n        {\"type\": \"currency\", \"description\": \"10 silver in hazard pay from the Dockers' Syndicate, stamped and counted at the House of Weights for the rescue under a singing sky.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"access\", \"description\": \"River Wardens day-pass to restricted chainhouse catwalks, granting lawful passage on maintenance and rescue routes while the investigation continues.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"reputation\", \"description\": \"Reputation: +Small with Dockers' Syndicate and River Wardens, earned by steady hands on a jammed lift and a clear head at Windward Bastion.\"}\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}"